- The virtual talks held by Russian and Ukrainian negotiators resumed on Tuesday. - The U.S. issued fresh Russia-related sanctions, including those on 15 individuals and one entity. - Ukraine's Verkhovna Rada, or parliament, has extended martial law in Ukraine from March 26 for 30 days. - Around 2.95 million people have fled Ukraine and crossed into other countries since the conflict in Ukraine began on February 24, the United Nations said Tuesday. - President of Belarus Alexander Lukashenko on Tuesday emphasized the importance of the Belarusian-Russian agreements reached at the governmental level, which were adopted on Monday as a follow-up to the negotiations between the heads of state.